	&lt;li&gt;The Constitution of Bhutan was enacted on &lt;strong&gt;18 July 2008 &lt;/strong&gt;by the Royal Government of Bhutan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bhutan&amp;#39;s political system has changed from an absolute monarchy to a &lt;strong&gt;constitutional monarchy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bhutan is the &lt;strong&gt;Sovereign Kingdom&lt;/strong&gt; and the Sovereign power belongs to the people of Bhutan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The current King of Bhutan is &lt;strong&gt;Jigme Khesar Namgyel Wangchuck.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On Dec 9, 2006, Jigme Khesar Namgyel Wangchuck became the king and is known as the&lt;strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;Dragon King&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; of Bhutan.&lt;/li&gt;
